---
description: Use these rules for API tests tasks
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use given (test setup) / when (tested action) / then (assertions) in tests provided as comments // given, // when, // then
- order API tests by response code ascending (200 -> 400 -> 401 -> 403 -> 404 -> etc.)
- use faker.js for generating random data
- use dedicated http clients (request objects): see http/loginRequest.ts and http/signupRequest.ts as examples
- do not create too many tests for validatione errors (400). Assume sufficient unit tests coverage for these cases.
- Once you create new tests run them via Playwright. Make sure they pass, iterate with fixes if needed. If you believe there is a bug in application leave the test as failing and let me know about it.